Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Soak your
@bamboo skewers{4} in cold water (this will prevent them from burning).

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, drain the @halloumi{225%g}, then cut it into 3cm chunks. Place into
a medium #bowl{} of cold water and leave to soak.

Lay the @British chicken thighs{3} flat onto a baking tray, drizzle with
@oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Rub in half the
@peri peri seasoning{2%sachets}, then set aside.

> Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into 2cm wide
strips, then cut into roughly 2cm pieces. Pop them into another medium bowl.

Remove the halloumi cubes from the cold water and drain the bowl. Pop the
cubes onto a #plate{} lined with #kitchen paper{} and pat them dry, then add
back to the bowl.

Add a drizzle of @oil{}, the remaining peri peri seasoning, @olive oil{1%tbsp}
for the marinade (see pantry for amount), then toss to coat.

Carefully thread the halloumi and pepper chunks onto the skewers (2 per person),
alternating between the two.

Once the wedges are about halfway through cooking and the chicken has around
12 mins left, pop the skewers onto the chicken baking tray.

Bake on the middle shelf until the chicken is cooked through, the halloumi is
golden and the pepper is tender, ~{10-12%minutes}.

> The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Creamy Lime Slaw ==

In the meantime, clean the medium bowls. Halve the @lime{1}.

In one bowl, combine the @coleslaw mix{120%g}, @mayonnaise{32%g} and half the
lime juice. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then set aside for later.

== Mango & Coriander Salsa ==

Peel the @mango{1}. Slice down either side of the stone to make 2 'cheeks'.
Cut any remaining flesh from the stone, then cut the mango into 1cm pieces
(discard the stone).

Roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch}(stalks and all).

In the other bowl, combine the mango, coriander and remaining lime juice.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== To Serve ==

When you have removed your chicken and halloumi skewers from the oven, drizzle
the @mango chutney{40%g} all over.

Share your sticky chicken thighs and halloumi skewers between your serving
plates.

Serve with your chips, coleslaw and salsa alongside. Enjoy!